Package: ubuntu-game-desktop
Source: ubuntu-game-session
Version: 0.5
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Ken VanDine <ken.vandine@canonical.com>
Installed-Size: 30
Depends: labwc, waybar, wofi, network-manager-gnome, fonts-noto
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Description: Ubuntu Gaming Desktop Session
 A lightweight Wayland desktop session (labwc + waybar + wofi) optimised for
 gaming on Ubuntu desktops and laptops. Games are launched via per-game
 gamescope wrappers, gaining frame-timing, upscaling, and HDR benefits without
 requiring a gamescope kiosk session.
 .
 Provides:
  - labwc floating Wayland compositor with keyboard shortcuts
  - waybar panel with app launcher, clock, Wi-Fi status and connection editor,
    battery indicator, and logout / reboot / shut-down buttons
  - wofi application launcher populated from installed .desktop files
  - nm-applet system-tray icon for network management
 .
 Unlike ubuntu-game-session (which runs Steam full-screen via gamescope),
 this session is a conventional windowed desktop suitable for desktops and
 laptops where a keyboard and pointer are available.
